Welcome to the Read group! I&#39;m glad to hear that a 10 year old is 
interested in the Alphabet. Keep us abreast of his progress.

You will find that this group - unlike the Shavians -  is not too 
hung up on the fine points of spelling.   It&#39;s just about 
communication, and you will know quickly if you are communicating.

While I&#39;m not from New York, I have lived there for 25 years, and 
recognize that, while there a great number of accents, for the most 
part they  are close to &quot;Middle Atlantic&quot; speech and will look the 
same in Read. It&#39;s not that you are from Louisiana or something.

You might also want to make some flash cards with Read words to work 
with your son.  And try keeping your shopping list in Read!





